<subSubSection id="95D9B2CC15EEEEA1D738FB1B487D044F" pageId="29" pageNumber="66" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="A3742DF3B7319A8556FEAE3E1A546FF0" pageId="29" pageNumber="66">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="59A018A96061AD02D7D6C1E5588406D7" pageId="29" pageNumber="66">We name this species after Edward G. Riley (retired), former collections manager at the Texas A &amp; M University Insect Collection, College Station, Texas. An invariable word in genitive.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
